3.Spatial Data Processing and Analysis

3.1Importing Community District Boundary Data

cd_shapefile_path <- "nycd_25d/nycd.shp"
nyc_cds_sf <- st_read(cd_shapefile_path, quiet = TRUE)

3.2Projection Matching and Spatial Join

nyc_cds_transformed <- st_transform(nyc_cds_sf, crs = 4326)
evictions_with_cd <- st_join(evictions_sf, nyc_cds_transformed, join = st_intersects, left = FALSE)
cat("Number of eviction points successfully joined to Community Districts: ", nrow(evictions_with_cd), "\n")
## Number of eviction points successfully joined to Community Districts:  2859

3.3Aggregate Counts by Community District

CD_IDENTIFIER_FIELD <- "BoroCD" 
cd_eviction_counts <- st_drop_geometry(evictions_with_cd) %>%
  group_by(CD_ID = .data[[CD_IDENTIFIER_FIELD]]) %>%
  summarise(Total_Evictions_2020 = n()) %>%
  ungroup()
cat("All involved community number: ", nrow(cd_eviction_counts), "\n")
## All involved community number:  59

3.4Merge Counts to Shapefile

final_evictions_map_data <- nyc_cds_transformed %>%
  select(BoroCD, Shape_Area) %>%
  left_join(cd_eviction_counts, by = c("BoroCD" = "CD_ID")) %>%
  mutate(Total_Evictions_2020 = replace_na(Total_Evictions_2020, 0))

3.7Local Gi Analysis and Classification

ENGLISH_LEVELS <- c(
  "Significant Hotspot (99% CI)",
  "Hotspot (95% CI)",
  "Not Significant",
  "Coldspot (95% CI)",
  "Significant Coldspot (99% CI)"
)

local_g_stars <- localG(final_evictions_map_data$Total_Evictions_2020, listw = queens_listw) 

final_evictions_map_data <- final_evictions_map_data %>%
  # 7a. Add Gi* Z scores to the spatial data
  mutate(Gi_Star_Z = as.numeric(local_g_stars)) %>%
  # 7b. Classify cluster type using English labels
  mutate(
    Gi_Star_Type = factor(case_when(
      Gi_Star_Z >= 2.58 ~ "Significant Hotspot (99% CI)",
      Gi_Star_Z <= -2.58 ~ "Significant Coldspot (99% CI)",
      Gi_Star_Z >= 1.96 ~ "Hotspot (95% CI)",
      Gi_Star_Z <= -1.96 ~ "Coldspot (95% CI)",
      TRUE ~ "Not Significant"
    ), 
    # Use ENGLISH_LEVELS to define factor order
    levels = ENGLISH_LEVELS 
    )
  )

cat("\n--- Local Getis-Ord Gi* Analysis Results ---\n")
## 
## --- Local Getis-Ord Gi* Analysis Results ---
print(head(st_drop_geometry(final_evictions_map_data) %>%
           select(BoroCD, Total_Evictions_2020, Gi_Star_Z, Gi_Star_Type)))

4.Extract and connect administrative regions

# --- Step 20: Extract and Join BOROUGH Information ---
# Ensure BOROUGH field is joined to final_evictions_map_data
if (!("BOROUGH" %in% names(final_evictions_map_data))) {
    # Assuming evictions_with_cd still exists
    borough_lookup <- st_drop_geometry(evictions_with_cd) %>%
        mutate(BOROUGH = str_to_title(BOROUGH)) %>% 
        select(BoroCD, BOROUGH) %>%
        distinct(BoroCD, .keep_all = TRUE) 

    final_evictions_map_data <- final_evictions_map_data %>% 
        left_join(borough_lookup, by = "BoroCD")
} else {
    final_evictions_map_data <- final_evictions_map_data
}

9.2 Cleaning and aggregating poverty data

poverty_file_name <- "NYC EH Data Portal - Neighborhood poverty (filtered).csv"
poverty_data_raw <- read_csv(poverty_file_name, show_col_types = FALSE) 

poverty_by_borough <- poverty_data_raw %>%
  # Select data categorized by 'Borough'
  filter(GeoTypeDesc == "Borough") %>%
  # Rename the poverty rate column and standardize the Borough format
  rename(Poverty_Rate = Percent) %>%
  mutate(BOROUGH = str_to_title(Borough)) %>%
  # Select only the required fields
  select(BOROUGH, Poverty_Rate)

9.3 Correlation analysis

# 1. Calculate Mean Evictions per Community District (CD) by Borough
evictions_by_borough <- st_drop_geometry(final_evictions_map_data) %>%
  # Assuming BOROUGH column is already present after Section 4 join
  filter(BOROUGH != "NA") %>% # Remove NA boroughs
  group_by(BOROUGH) %>%
  summarise(
    Mean_Evictions_per_CD = mean(Total_Evictions_2020) # Average evictions per CD
  )

# 2. Merge data frames
correlation_data <- evictions_by_borough %>%
  # Join evictions data with poverty data by 'BOROUGH'
  left_join(poverty_by_borough, by = "BOROUGH")

# 3. Calculate Pearson Correlation Coefficient
correlation_result <- cor.test(correlation_data$Mean_Evictions_per_CD, 
                               correlation_data$Poverty_Rate, 
                               method = "pearson")

cat("\n--- Correlation Analysis: Mean Evictions vs. Poverty Rate (Borough Level) ---\n")
## 
## --- Correlation Analysis: Mean Evictions vs. Poverty Rate (Borough Level) ---
print(correlation_result)
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  correlation_data$Mean_Evictions_per_CD and correlation_data$Poverty_Rate
## t = 4.2109, df = 3, p-value = 0.02446
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.2311884 0.9951258
## sample estimates:
##       cor 
## 0.9248196

10. Visual scatter plot

correlation_plot_fixed <- ggplot(correlation_data, 
                               aes(x = Poverty_Rate, y = Mean_Evictions_per_CD)) + # Removed label from global aes
  geom_point(size = 3, aes(color = BOROUGH)) +
  
  # Add linear regression line (no standard error)
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "gray") +
  
  # Add Borough labels next to the points, using geom_text
  geom_text(aes(label = BOROUGH), vjust = -1, size = 3) + 
  
  labs(title = "Evictions vs. Poverty Rate by Borough (2020)",
       x = "Poverty Rate (%)",
       y = "Mean Evictions per Community District") +
  theme_minimal()

print(correlation_plot_fixed)

race_file_name <- "NYC EH Data Portal - Race and ethnicity.csv"
race_raw_data <- read_csv(race_file_name, show_col_types = FALSE) 

race_all_data <- race_raw_data %>%
  
  filter(GeoType == "Borough") %>% 
  mutate(BOROUGH = str_to_title(Geography)) %>%
  
  select(BOROUGH, ends_with("(percent)")) %>%
  
  pivot_longer(
    cols = ends_with("(percent)"),
    names_to = "Race_Category",
    values_to = "Race_Percentage"
  )

13.Merge and visualize all racial relevance

correlation_data_all_race <- evictions_by_borough %>%
  left_join(race_all_data, by = "BOROUGH")

correlation_plot_all_race <- ggplot(correlation_data_all_race, 
                               aes(x = Race_Percentage, y = Mean_Evictions_per_CD, color = BOROUGH)) +
  
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "gray50", size = 0.5) + 
  
  facet_wrap(~ Race_Category, scales = "free_x") + 
  
  labs(
    title = "Evictions vs. Race/Ethnicity Percentage by Borough (2020)",
    x = "Population Percentage (%)",
    y = "Mean Evictions per Community District"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    strip.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
    legend.position = "bottom"
  )

14.Mapping Hispanic people

race_percent_map_data <- correlation_data_all_race %>%
  filter(Race_Category == "Hispanic alone (percent)") %>%
  rename(Hispanic_Percent = Race_Percentage) %>%
  select(BOROUGH, Hispanic_Percent)


map_data_race <- final_evictions_map_data %>%
  
  select(BoroCD, BOROUGH, geometry) %>%
  left_join(race_percent_map_data, by = "BOROUGH")


map_hispanic_percent <- ggplot(map_data_race) +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = Hispanic_Percent), 
          color = "gray80", 
          size = 0.3) +

  scale_fill_continuous(low = "lightyellow", 
                        high = "darkred", 
                        name = "Hispanic Population\nPercentage (%)",
                        labels = scales::comma,
                        na.value = "gray90") + 
  
  theme_void() + 
  theme(
    legend.position = "right",
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold", size = 14),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  
  labs(
    title = "Map F: Hispanic Population (2020)",
    subtitle = "Visual Evidence for Racial Disparity"
  )

print(map_hispanic_percent)

15.Mapping Black people

black_percent_map_data <- race_all_data %>%
  
  filter(Race_Category == "Black alone (percent)") %>%
  rename(Black_Percent = Race_Percentage) %>%
  select(BOROUGH, Black_Percent)


map_data_black <- final_evictions_map_data %>%

  select(BoroCD, BOROUGH, geometry) %>%
  left_join(black_percent_map_data, by = "BOROUGH")
